        {
            "title": "GigaDevice Semiconductor Shares Jump on Trading Debut",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>\n  By Sherry Qin </p><br/><p>\n  Shares of GigaDevice Semiconductor surged on its trading debut in Hong Kong, joining a growing list of Chinese artificial intelligence and chip companies tapping the financial hub for capital in recent months. </p><!-- Article --><p>\n\n  The Beijing-based chip maker's shares rose 47% early Tuesday to 237.00 Hong Kong dollars from its listing price of HK$162.00 per share. The company, which specializes in making memory chips and microcontrollers, raised 4.68 billion Hong Kong dollars in gross proceeds, or US$600.3 million. </p><p>\n\n  Its Shanghai-listed shares increased 2.6% to 268.00 yuan. </p><p>\n\n  Chinese chip makers and AI startups have stepped up efforts to go public in a city that is experiencing an IPO revival after a yearslong drought. </p><p>\n\n  GigaDevice's listing follows blockbuster debuts by AI chip maker Shanghai Biren Technology and AI startups MiniMax and Knowledge Atlas Technology, which is better known as Zhipu AI. </p><p>\n\n  China's AI progress and efforts to achieve tech self-reliance have boosted investor sentiment. The daily volume for stock markets in Shanghai, Shenzhen and Beijing reached a record high of 3.64 trillion yuan, equivalent to US$522 billion, on Monday, according to data from financial platform Wind Information. </p><p>\n\n  GigaDevice's 2024 net profit jumped almost seven fold while revenue rose 28% to 7.36 billion yuan as the global semiconductor industry emerged from a pandemic-era glut and prices of its products in end market started to recover. </p><p>\n\n  The company could benefit from surging prices for memory chips, which made up around 70% of its 2024 revenue, as analysts expect supply will remain restrained this year amid the AI boom. </p><p>\n\n  GigaDevice expects the increasing adoption of AI in devices to drive the demand of its products, which are mostly used in consumer electronics and automotive electronics. </p><p>\n\n  Write to Sherry Qin at sherry.qin@wsj.com </p><br/><p>\n  (END) Dow Jones Newswires</p><p>\n\n  01-12-26 2223ET</p></div>",
            "link": "https://hk.marketscreener.com/news/gigadevice-semiconductor-shares-jump-on-trading-debut-ce7e58dbd88bfe24",
            "pub_date": "2026-01-13 11:25:48",
            "source": "marketscreener",
            "kind": 1,
            "language": "en"
